Privacy Policy for RPT
Effective Date: July 22, 2026

Introduction
RPT is a local-first strength training app for reverse pyramid training. This policy explains what information the app handles, where it stays, and what leaves the device.

No Accounts, Tracking, or Analytics
RPT does not require an account. We do not run third-party analytics, advertising SDKs, tracking SDKs, or crash-reporting SDKs in the app binary. The app does not track you across apps or websites.

Information You Enter in the App
You may enter training information such as workout logs, exercise names, weights, repetitions, RPE values, templates, timer preferences, and app settings. This information is stored locally on your device using Apple's on-device storage systems. We do not operate a server that receives or stores your workout data.

Device Storage and UserDefaults
RPT uses on-device storage, including UserDefaults, for app preferences, onboarding state, rest-timer settings, and workout-state recovery. This data remains on your device unless you export it yourself, delete it, reset app data, or remove the app.

CSV Export
If you choose to export your workout history, RPT creates a CSV file locally and opens the iOS share sheet. You control where that exported file goes. Exporting is a user-initiated action.

Purchases and Restore Purchases
RPT Pro purchase and restore actions are handled by Apple's StoreKit and the App Store. Apple may process purchase information under Apple's own terms and privacy policy. RPT uses StoreKit only to determine whether the RPT Pro entitlement is unlocked; we do not receive your payment card details.

Data Collection Disclosure
For App Store privacy purposes, RPT is designed so the developer does not collect data from the app. Training data, preferences, and exported files stay under your control on your device unless you intentionally share them outside the app.

Third-Party Services
RPT does not integrate Apple Health, location services, contacts, camera, photo library, advertising networks, or third-party analytics SDKs in the current app binary. The App Store purchase flow is provided by Apple.

Children's Privacy
RPT is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

Deleting Your Data
You can delete RPT data by using any in-app reset options that are available, deleting exported files you created, or deleting the app from your device.

Changes to This Policy
We may update this policy as the app changes. The effective date above will be updated when the policy changes.

